            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the dish with your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>five-spice mix</strong> (not a fan of five spice? Only add a little!), <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil, then add the <strong>pork belly</strong> to the dish, skin-side up</p><p>Put the dish in the oven and cook, uncovered, for an initial 40 min or until the sauce has thickened and the pork is golden brown</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1642000715583-x200.jpg",
